    "Terence E. Fretheim, Thomas B. Slater": "), those who are alert to threats\nto a city and provide warning through the blowing of the trumpet\n(see 4:5, 19, 21; 6:1), has reference to the prophets in particular\n[v_Ezk_3_16] [v_Ezk_3_17] [v_Ezk_3_18] [v_Ezk_3_19] [v_Ezk_3_20] [v_Ezk_3_21] (see Ezek 3:16-21; Hos 9:8). Once again, God\u2019s graciousness is evi-\ndent, warning the people of possible threats to their life. But again,\neven after having heard the trumpet sound associated with war,\nthey ignore it (see 7:25-26).\nThese rejections of God\u2019s gracious provisions along the journey\nof Israel\u2019s life issue in an announcement of judgment (\nv. 17; 2:34; 5:26-28; 7:6; 19:4 and\n[v_Jer_22_1] Jeremiah 22:1\u201323:8\n316\n317\n[v_Jer_22_1] Jeremiah 22:1\u201323:8\n[v_Deu_27_25] the curse in Deut 27:25; Jeremiah appeals to this command when\nhis life is threatened, 26:15).\nThe \u201ceither-or\u201d address in vv. 4-5 is common in Jeremiah (see"
